cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of reconstructing 3D object shapes from a single image, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The approach involves using a deep autoencoder to learn a set of latent codes of 3D object shapes, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using image cues and silhouette to guide the optimization process, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM).
